        <Summary>Conductor and Reduction Types for Genus 2 Curves</Summary>
        <Description>Let C be a proper smooth curve of genus 2 defined by a hyperelliptic equation y^2+Q(x)y=P(x) where P(x) and Q(x) are polynomials with rational coefficients such that deg(Q(x))&lt;5, deg(P(x))&lt;8. Let J(C) be the Jacobian of C, let X be the minimal regular model of C over the ring of integers Z. This program determines the reduction of C at any prime number p (that is the special fiber X_p of X over p), and the exponent f of the conductor of J(C) at p.</Description>
        <Archive sha1sum="14f42561d654fc5c3f177f68cb7142baa990aefe" type="targz">http://www.math.u-bordeaux.fr/~liu/G2R/genus2reduction-0.3.tar.gz</Archive>
